# C++ basics One shot 


1. **Skeleton/Basic Structure of C++ program**

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    cout << "Hello, World!" << endl << "Hello Miller" << endl;
    return 0;
}


## \n is faster than endl; still in college and everywhere we use endl more often , why ???


2. **Basic input/output **

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    int x,y;
    cin>>x>>y;
    cout << "The value of x is " << x << " and y is " << y ;
    return 0;
}

/////complete the function printNumber which takes an integer input from the user and prints it on the screen
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int printNumber(int x)
{
    cin >> x ;
    cout << x ;

}

int main()
{

int x;

int y;

printNumber(x);

cout << endl;

printNumber(y);

return 0;

}


